ground-color: #ccc;"> lost a proxy fight</a>=C2=A0to a tiny activist that w=
anted it to speed up its transition away from fossil fuels.</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">Now, to be clear, all of these trends can be described in =
terms of shareholder value. Being nice to stakeholders and having a purpose=
 and being environmentally friendly and so forth are all things that probab=
ly improve the long-term sustainability and profitability=C2=A0of a company=
, and shareholders can prefer them for purely financial reasons. Still they=
 seem to have some independent weight in modern corporate thought. The Busi=
ness Roundtable CEOs want to weigh the interests of all stakeholders and so=
metimes=C2=A0<em>prefer=C2=A0</em>other stakeholders over shareholders; at =
least some ESG investors are surely <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/27570320.267604/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXFyLmNvbS9JbnNpZ2h0cy9QZ=
XJzcGVjdGl2ZXMvVmlydHVlLWlzLWl0cy1Pd24tUmV3YXJkLU9yLU9uZS1NYW5zLUNlaWxpbmct=
