</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If a Brazilian iron mining company bui=
lds a dam, and the dam collapses, kills 270 people and causes =E2=80=9Cimme=
asurable environmental and social harm,=E2=80=9D is that securities fraud? =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27570320.267604/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMi03Mg/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB2ed2cb5b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">Of course it is</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission [Thurssday] cha=
rged Vale S.A., a publicly traded Brazilian mining company and one of the w=
orld=E2=80=99s largest iron ore producers, with making false and misleading=
 claims about the safety of its dams prior to the January 2019 collapse of =
its Brumadinho dam. The collapse killed 270 people, caused immeasurable env=
ironmental and social harm, and led to a loss of more than $4 billion in Va=
le=E2=80=99s market capitalization.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A=
ccording to the SEC=E2=80=99s complaint, beginning in 2016, Vale manipulate=
d multiple dam safety audits; obtained numerous fraudulent stability certif=
icates; and regularly misled local governments, communities, and investors =
about the safety of the Brumadinho dam through its environmental, social, a=
nd governance (ESG) disclosures. The SEC=E2=80=99s complaint also alleges t=
hat, for years, Vale knew that the Brumadinho dam, which was built to conta=
in potentially toxic byproducts from mining operations, did not meet intern=
ationally-recognized standards for dam safety. However, Vale=E2=80=99s publ=
ic Sustainability Reports and other public filings fraudulently assured inv=
estors that the company adhered to the =E2=80=9Cstrictest international pra=
ctices=E2=80=9D in evaluating dam safety and that 100 percent of its dams w=
ere certified to be in stable condition.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">This is all pretty normal stuff. As I <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27570320.267604/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMDMvZ29sZG1hbi1zYWNocy1nb2VzLXRvLXN=
1cHJlbWUtY291cnQtaGVkZ2UtZnVuZHMtd29uLW9uLWdhbWVzdG9wLWtrcG9lNndzP2NtcGlkPU=
JCRDA1MDIyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0d=
GVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDUwMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cB23dc3fba" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;"> often say around here</a>, every bad thing that =
a public company does, or that happens to a public company, can be recharac=
terized as securities fraud: (1) you said your dams were safe, (2) I bought=
 the stock, (3) a dam collapsed, (4) the stock went down.=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But there are two somewhat unusual points here. One is=
 that Vale is a Brazilian company and the dam was in Brazil, so it=E2=80=99=
s a bit odd for the U.S. SEC to regulate it. But Vale has American deposito=
ry receipts that trade on the New York Stock Exchange, and also sold bonds =
in the U.S., and that=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/27570320.267604/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMDYtMjYvZXZlcnl0aGluZy1ldmVyeXdoZXJlLWlzLXNlY3VyaXRpZXMt=
ZnJhdWQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUwMjIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc29=
1cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNTAyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBee700809" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> more than good enough</a> for th=
e SEC. When a Brazilian company=E2=80=99s dam in Brazil collapses and kills=
 270 Brazilians, the SEC will step in to protect American shareholders.</p>=
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The other point is that, as the press release =
says,=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cthe SEC announced in March 2021 the formation of a Clim=
ate and ESG Task Force in the Division of Enforcement with a mandate to ide=
ntify material gaps or misstatements in issuers=E2=80=99 ESG disclosures, l=
ike the false and misleading claims made by Vale.=E2=80=9D Presumably most =
companies=E2=80=99 incorrect environmental, social and governance disclosur=
es will not lead to 270 deaths and wipe out $4 billion of market capitaliza=
tion. But the SEC is, as it were, staking a claim on them; it is telling co=
mpanies =E2=80=9Cwe will read your ESG disclosures, and if they=E2=80=99re =
wrong then that=E2=80=99s securities fraud just like everything else and we=
 will come after you.=E2=80=9D</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" bo=
